spanGrp.span: Here in our land, Ujarraz, the children and the grandparents did not live very well.
Jiska se je kã' Uja(r) Ujarras ñãyigira se je yabla-la tatiga-la mamita wa jie-wa të (_) kã' ñã' jiñã jiska suruwi jie-wa senã' ka rö böiuna
They had to walk all the way to Buenos Aires;
Jie-wa jenã shkö klö wa dömiũ Buenos Aires
it was not like nowadays that we can go to Buenos Aires by bus.
jie-wa dögẽgau-lo-nẽ ka rö jira bi se je shkö-gẽ se mi-gẽ Buenos Aires pe tebeli_yaga inga
We leave in the morning and come back at noon, or in the afternoon.
se dögẽgau-nẽ se migẽũ señira se dögẽgau-nẽ kawö mõ inga sino komĩskla wa
Long ago there was nothing like that;
long ago our grandparents and aunts used to walk to Buenos Aires, back and forth.
ñãyegira (eh) mamita-la tia-la shkö-gẽ klö wa demĩũ diá Buenos Aires í dögẽgau-lo-nẽ
There were lots of trees, but people cut them off.
kã' rö kal wa ebö Je kable ka í ta ĩã Pe të í tiátlá-mĩ
I think that we... long ago they walked;
Yís të í begetse ke se je të se je ñayigi jie-wa shkaĩã jira ka í ta ĩã
We won’t won’t won’t seee them like they used to be.
(_) Kai kai kai (_) ka se sunã ñãyigi bi
